docs.summary: Describes the catalog integration to be called by Wix and received by the relevant catalog provider. This integration is used to interface between the Wix eCommerce platform and externally managed repositories of sellable items.

params.name: catalogReferences
params.doc: Catalog reference details for the items to retrieve, including quantity of each item.

params.name: weightUnit
params.doc:
Weight measurement unit. 

 By default, Wix sends the weight unit specified in the site's settings.

params.name: currency
params.doc:
Currency to return item prices in, in [ISO 4217](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) format. For example, `USD` or `EUR`.

 By default, Wix sends the currency specified in the site's settings.

docs.summary:
Retrieves data for specified items in a specified catalog.

 Wix calls this endpoint whenever a cart or checkout is updated, and when an item is added to an order.
 
 The endpoint receives a `catalogReferences` array. Each catalog reference in the array contains: 
 + The ID of the item whose latest information Wix needs to retrieve.
 + The ID of the app providing the catalog containing the item.
 + Optional details about preferences or customization of the item.

 The endpoint also receives preferences for the currency and weight unit to be used in the response.

 Your external catalog can store and organize item details in any way you prefer.
 When implementing the Catalog SPI, learn how to [handle item variants](../../../../docs/Catalog-Reference.md) in a way that meets your needs.

 The endpoint's response must contain a `catalogItems` array. Each item in the array must contain:
 + A `catalogReference` object. This must be identical to the `catalogReference` object received in the request.
 + A `data` object with full details about the item.

 > **Notes:**
 > + If an item doesn't exist in the catalog, the response must exclude it from the `catalogItems` array in the response. 
 > + When none of the items requested exist in the catalog, `catalogItems` must contain an empty array.
 > + Wix calls the endpoint every time a cart or checkout is updated. If the response doesn't include an item that was already in the cart or checkout, Wix removes the item from the cart or checkout.

docs.summary: Used for grouping line items. Sent when an item is added to a cart, checkout, or order.

members.name: catalogItemId
members.doc: ID of the item within the catalog it belongs to.

members.name: appId
members.doc:
ID of the app providing the catalog.

You can get your app's ID from its page in the [Wix Dev Center](https://dev.wix.com/apps).

For items from Wix catalogs, the following values always apply:
+ Wix Stores: `"215238eb-22a5-4c36-9e7b-e7c08025e04e"`
+ Wix Bookings: `"13d21c63-b5ec-5912-8397-c3a5ddb27a97"`
+ Wix Restaurants: `"9a5d83fd-8570-482e-81ab-cfa88942ee60"`

members.name: options
members.doc:
Additional item details in key:value pairs.

 Use this optional field to specify a variant of the item or add custom details. There are several ways to use `options`:
 + Pass specific information about the item variant in this field. For example, size and color of an item of clothing: `"options": {"Size": "M", "Color": "Red"}`.
 + Create a separate API for creating item variants that stores the details and generates a unique ID for each item variant. Then pass only the variant ID in this field. For example: `"options": {"variantId": "<VARIANT_ID>"}`.

 Given a full image URL of `https://static.wixstatic.com/media/5cc69183e7954e2c9760fa2383870992.jpg`, `media.id` is `5cc69183e7954e2c9760fa2383870992.jpg`.

members.doc:
Date and time the service is to be provided, in [ISO-8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Combined_date_and_time_representations) format.
 For example, the start time of a class.

members.name: numberOfParticipants
members.doc: The number of people participating in the service. For example, the number of people attending a class or the number of people per hotel room.

members.name: original
members.doc: __Required.__ Price description in the site's default language.

members.name: translated
members.doc:
Price description translated into the buyer's language.

 Default: Same as `original`.

members.name: name
members.doc: Coupon scope's group (e.g., product or collection in Wix Stores). See [valid scope values](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/coupons/coupons/valid-scope-values).

members.name: entityId
members.doc: Item ID (when the coupon scope is limited to just one item).

members.name: namespace
members.doc: Scope namespace (Wix Stores, Wix Bookings, Wix Events, Wix Pricing Plans)

members.name: group
members.doc: Coupon scope's applied group (e.g., event or ticket in Wix Events)

members.name: productName
members.doc: __Required.__ Item name.

members.name: url
members.doc:
URL for the item's page on the site. 

 This is used to link back to the relevant item page from the cart page. If not provided, the site URL is used.

members.name: itemType
members.doc: __Required.__ Item type. Either one of the preset types or a custom type.

members.name: price
members.doc: __Required.__ Item price with discounts applied. If a catalog-defined discount applies, the discount is reflected in this price.

members.name: fullPrice
members.doc:
Item price **before** applying any catalog-defined discount.

 Default: Value of `price` field, if no catalog-defined discount applies.

members.name: taxGroupId
members.doc: The tax group ID associated with this item.

members.name: descriptionLines
members.doc:
Line item description lines. Used for displaying the item in a cart, checkout or order. For example, if you want `Size: Large` to appear under the item name, create a description line with `"name": {"original": "Size"}` and  `"plainText": {"original": "Large"}`.

 Default: No description line.

members.name: media
members.doc:
Line item image details. Supports images from the [Wix Media Manager](https://support.wix.com/en/article/wix-media-accessing-the-media-manager) only. 

 To use an image from another source, first upload it to the Media Manager. 
 You can retrieve the ID, width and height of an image from the Wix Media Manager.

members.name: quantityAvailable
members.doc:
Quantity of the item available for purchase. Only return if the catalog manages inventory. 
 If not returned, a buyer can increase the quantity of this item to add to the cart or checkout without limit.

members.name: physicalProperties
members.doc: Physical properties of the item. Only return for physical items. When applicable, contains information such as SKU and item weight.

members.name: paymentOption
members.doc:
Payment method selected for the item.
 
 + `FULL_PAYMENT_ONLINE`: The entire payment for this item happens as part of the checkout.
 + `FULL_PAYMENT_OFFLINE`: The entire payment for this item happens after the checkout. For example, when using cash, check, or other offline payment methods. 
 + `MEMBERSHIP`: Payment for this item is done by charging a membership. When selected, `price` is `0`.
 + `DEPOSIT_ONLINE`: Partial payment to be paid upfront during the checkout. Initial amount to be paid for each line item is specified in `depositAmount`.
 + `MEMBERSHIP_OFFLINE`: Payment for this item can only be done by charging a membership and must be manually redeemed in the dashboard by the site admin. When selected, `price` is `0`.

 Default: `FULL_PAYMENT_ONLINE`.

members.name: serviceProperties
members.doc: Service properties. When applicable, this contains information such as time and number of participants.

members.name: rootCatalogItemId
members.doc:
Additional ID for the item in the catalog.
 This field provides an additional identifier for the item if your flow requires another ID as well as `catalogReference.catalogItemId`.
 Can be used for membership validation.

 Default: Same as `catalogReference.catalogItemId`.

members.name: priceDescription
members.doc:
Additional description for the price. Return when additional information about the price is needed.

 For example, when `price` is `"0"` but additional details about the actual price are needed, such as `"Starts at $67"`.

members.name: depositAmount
members.doc:
Partial payment to be paid upfront during the checkout. Return when `paymentOption` is `DEPOSIT_ONLINE`.

 Default: If `paymentOption` is `DEPOSIT_ONLINE` but `depositAmount` is not provided, the item is treated as if `paymentOption` is `FULL_PAYMENT_ONLINE`.

members.doc: Number of items returned in the response.

members.name: total
members.doc: Total number of items that match the query.

members.name: tooManyToCount
members.doc: Flag that indicates the server failed to calculate the `total` field.

 By default, Wix sends the weight unit specified in the site's settings.

members.name: currency
members.doc:
Currency to return item prices in, in [ISO 4217](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217) format. For example, `USD` or `EUR`.

 By default, Wix sends the currency specified in the site's settings.

members.name: catalogItems
members.doc:
Details for each item, including catalog reference details and item data. Any items that don't exist in the catalog are excluded.
 If none of the requested items exist in the catalog, this array must be empty.

members.name: catalogReference
members.doc: Catalog and item reference info. Holds IDs for the item and the catalog it belongs to, as well as further optional details. This is identical in the request and response.

members.name: quantity
members.doc: Item quantity.

members.name: catalogReference
members.doc: Catalog and item reference info. Holds IDs for the item and the catalog it belongs to, as well as further optional details. This is identical in the request and response.

members.name: data
members.doc: Item data. Contains full details about the item.

members.name: catalogItemIds
members.doc: A list of itemIDs to filter by. If exists, the result will only include the items with the IDs passed.

members.name: catalogItemName
members.doc: An item name to filter by. If exists, the result will only include items with name that starts with this string.

members.name: paging
members.doc: Paging options to limit and skip a number of items.

Optional, if exist add filter by numericId gt last_numeric_id

docs.summary:
Possible values are:
  • UNRECOGNISED
  • PLAIN_TEXT
  • COLOR

Frequency unit of recurring payment Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • DAY
  • WEEK
  • MONTH
  • YEAR

Possible values are:
  • UNRECOGNISED
  • PHYSICAL
  • DIGITAL
  • GIFT_CARD
  • SERVICE

Possible values are:
  • UNSPECIFIED
  • SECURE_PICTURE
  • SECURE_VIDEO
  • SECURE_DOCUMENT
  • SECURE_MUSIC
  • SECURE_ARCHIVE

Type of selected payment option for catalog item Possible values are:
  • FULL_PAYMENT_ONLINE - The entire payment for this item happens as part of the checkout.
  • FULL_PAYMENT_OFFLINE - The entire payment for this item happens after the checkout. For example, when using cash, check, or other offline payment methods.
  • MEMBERSHIP - Payment for this item is done by charging a membership. When selected, `price` is `0`.
  • DEPOSIT_ONLINE - Partial payment to be paid upfront during the checkout. Initial amount to be paid for each line item is specified in `depositAmount`.
  • MEMBERSHIP_OFFLINE - Payment for this item can only be done by charging a membership and must be manually redeemed in the dashboard by the site admin. When selected, `price` is `0`.

Possible values are:
  • UNSPECIFIED_WEIGHT_UNIT - Weight unit can't be classified, due to an error
  • KG - Kilograms
  • LB - Pounds
